full story of how this influential group shifted the course of philosophy in America. In addition to pioneering pragmatism, the group explored radical empiricism and idealism, and formulated personalism and process philosophy, equally important developments. This volume contains the important writings dating from 1870 to 1885 by the real members of the Metaphysical Club. The first section centers on pragmatism and science; the second part collects writings of the lawyers; and the third part covers idealist and personalist philosophers. Many of these writings have never been reprinted before, and nothing like this impressive collection has ever been attempted. A general introduction provides a narrative history, and the editors' three introductions to the volume's sections vividly bring to life the intense meetings, sustained debates, and pioneering thought of the Metaphysical Club.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPhilosophy, Americany19th century. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 4aPhilosophy : American Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Pragmatism. 4aPhilosophy : Process Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aButler, Brian E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aButler, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGood, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGood, James A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRyan, Frank X., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyan, Frank X., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShook, John R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://doi.org